{
  "texts": [
    "This architectural evolution gives rise to a new network named HSCNN-D, substantially augmenting the network's structural complexity to attain heightened precision.",
    "The empirical results unequivocally highlight the substantial progress our proposed models bring about, advancing the existing state-of-the-art in hyperspectral reconstruction.",
    "The SRLWRDNet model adopts a dual-network strategy, simultaneously extracting unique features from an input image through parallel processing (Nathan et al. 2020).",
    "These features are then merged to improve the quality of image reconstruction.",
    "Initially, the image is processed through a coordinate convolutional layer, adding two extra channels to highlight boundary details and reduce internal inconsistencies, standardizing values between -1 and 1."
  ]
}